@startuml Seq03_StatementUpload
!theme plain
participant User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "FastAPI Backend" as Backend
participant "File Parser\n(Pandas)" as Parser
participant "Data Cleaner" as Cleaner
participant "Categorizer" as Categorizer
participant "MySQL Database" as DB

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **FILE UPLOAD & PARSING**

User -> Frontend: Navigate to upload page
Frontend -> Frontend: Display file upload interface

User -> Frontend: Click "Select File"
Frontend -> Frontend: Open file picker
User -> Frontend: Select CSV/Excel file

Frontend -> Frontend: Validate file
alt Valid File Type
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show file name
    User -> Frontend: Click "Preview"
    
    Frontend -> Backend: POST /upload/preview\n(multipart/form-data file)
    
    Backend -> Parser: parse_file(file)
    alt File is CSV
        Parser -> Parser: Use pandas.read_csv()
    else File is Excel
        Parser -> Parser: Use pandas.read_excel()
    end
    
    Parser --> Backend: [raw_data: [...rows...]]
    
    Backend -> Frontend: {preview: [...first 5 rows...]}\nExpected columns: date, description, amount, type
    Frontend -> Frontend: Render preview table
    
    Frontend --> User: Show preview with sample data
    
else Invalid File
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show error message
    Frontend --> User: Please upload CSV or Excel
end

Note over User,DB: **DATA CLEANING & EXTRACTION**

User -> Frontend: Confirm data looks good
User -> Frontend: Click "Upload"

Frontend -> Backend: POST /upload/statement\n(multipart/form-data)

Backend -> Parser: extract_transactions(file)
Parser --> Backend: [raw_transactions]

Backend -> Cleaner: clean_data([transactions])

Note over Cleaner: Data Cleaning:
Note over Cleaner: - Remove duplicates
Note over Cleaner: - Handle null values
Note over Cleaner: - Standardize date format
Note over Cleaner: - Remove special chars
Note over Cleaner: - Normalize amounts

Cleaner -> Cleaner: remove_duplicates()
Cleaner -> Cleaner: handle_nulls()
Cleaner -> Cleaner: standardize_dates()
Cleaner -> Cleaner: normalize_amounts()

Cleaner --> Backend: [cleaned_transactions]

Backend -> Frontend: {status: "processing", processed: 45, total: 47}
Frontend -> Frontend: Show progress

Note over User,DB: **AUTO-CATEGORIZATION**

Backend -> Categorizer: categorize_batch([transactions])

loop For Each Transaction
    Categorizer -> Categorizer: Check rule-based keywords
    alt Category Found
        Categorizer -> Categorizer: Assign category
    else No Match
        Categorizer -> Categorizer: Send to LLM
        Categorizer -> Categorizer: Get AI category
    end
end

Categorizer --> Backend: [categorized_transactions]

Backend -> Frontend: {status: "saving", categorized: 47}

Note over User,DB: **BULK INSERT TO DATABASE**

Backend -> DB: bulk INSERT INTO transactions\nVALUES (...transaction1...),\n(...transaction2...),\n...(all 47 transactions)...

DB --> Backend: {rows_inserted: 47, success}

Backend -> Frontend: {status: "success",\ntotal_uploaded: 47,\ncategories_detected: {...summary...}}

Frontend -> Frontend: Hide loading spinner
Frontend -> Frontend: Show success summary

Note over Frontend: Summary shown:
Note over Frontend: - Total transactions: 47
Note over Frontend: - Food: 12
Note over Frontend: - Transport: 8
Note over Frontend: - Shopping: 10
Note over Frontend: - Bills: 10
Note over Frontend: - Entertainment: 7

Frontend -> Frontend: Show upload history option
Frontend --> User: Upload completed successfully!

Note over User,DB: **VIEW UPLOAD HISTORY**

User -> Frontend: Click "Upload History"
Frontend -> Backend: GET /upload/history

Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM uploaded_files\nWHERE user_id={user_id}\nORDER BY upload_date DESC
DB --> Backend: [file1, file2, file3, ...]

Backend --> Frontend: {uploads: [...]}
Frontend -> Frontend: Render upload history table
Frontend --> User: Show all uploaded files

Note over User,DB: **ERROR HANDLING**

alt File Parsing Error
    Parser --> Backend: {error: "Invalid CSV format"}
    Backend --> Frontend: {error: "File format invalid"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show error message
    Frontend --> User: Cannot parse file
else Duplicate Detection
    Backend -> Backend: Check for duplicates
    Backend -> Frontend: {warning: "10 duplicates found",\naction: "skip/merge?"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show options
    User -> Frontend: Choose action
else Categorization Error
    Categorizer --> Backend: {error: "LLM API error"}
    Backend -> Frontend: {partial_success: true,\nerrors: [...]}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show partial success
end

@enduml
